    "To evaluate the reliability of ANI-1xnr in practical research scenarios, we conduct several condensed-phase reactive chemistry simulations inspired by other literature with the ANI-1xnr potential, namely carbon solid-phase nucleation [46] [47] [48], graphene ring formation from acetylene with varying O 2 concentrations 44, 49, biodiesel ignition with different fuel additives 50, methane combustion 24 and the spontaneous formation of glycine from early earth molecules 44, 51, 52."
